1. Tag: 
Syntax: <tagname>content</tagname>
For example paragraphs use the p tag so we create hello world using <p>Hello World</p>
Some tags don't have a closing tag like horizontal rules: <hr> or <hr/>

2. Attribute: 
Provides extra info to html elements. 
Syntax: <tagname attribute="value">content</tagname> for example: <input type="checkboc" />

3. <!Doctype html>
This is the first line of every html file for telling browser which version of html to use, A doctype will use modern html5 standard. 
While a page would usually render without doctype, they should always be included as some older browsers will not render pages following modern specifications without it. 

4. <head>

Tha tag containing metadata about the HTML document. The <title> is the only required tag within the <head>. 
This gives the page a title which is used by browsers to name the tab and it also gets used for search results in many search engines.

5. <body>
The tag that contains the content of the webpage. 


<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <title>My First Webpage</title>
  </head>
  <body>
    <p>Hello World!</p>
  </body>
</html>
